spec: asyncio_extra72
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html — Python asyncio module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-sync.html — asyncio Synchronization Primitives"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-task.html — asyncio Tasks and Coroutines"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/__init__.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/locks.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/taskgroups.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/tasks.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends asyncio_extra71.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: asyncio.__name__/__package__, Queue/Lock/Event/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore/Condition __name__/__module__/__qualname__, Task/Future __name__/__module__/__qualname__/__class__.__name__, CancelledError/InvalidStateError/TimeoutError identity, QueueEmpty/QueueFull identity, gather/sleep/wait/__name__/__qualname__, class __dict__/__mro__/__all__ metadata, method qualname/name equality and length tables, __loader__/__spec__/__file__/__cached__ class names, __spec__ attributes, code object attribute chains, __defaults__/__kwdefaults__ class names, exception hierarchy and module identity, module spec and synchronization class doc content, Queue/Lock/Event/Semaphore __init__ code object attributes."
    - "This spec covers (asyncioann72 namespace): wave 238 theme — asyncio class __annotations__ and Condition/BoundedSemaphore __init__ code objects. NEW in extra72: Condition.__init__.__code__.co_name=='__init__'; Condition.__init__.__code__.co_argcount==2 (self + lock=None); BoundedSemaphore.__init__.__code__.co_name=='__init__'; BoundedSemaphore.__init__.__code__.co_argcount==2 (self + value=1); TaskGroup.__name__=='TaskGroup'; TaskGroup.__module__=='asyncio.taskgroups'; TaskGroup.__qualname__=='TaskGroup'; TaskGroup.__bases__[0].__name__=='object'; TaskGroup.__mro__.__len__()==2; gather.__code__.co_name=='gather'. gather is a pure Python async function; gather.__code__.co_argcount==0 (all args are *coros_or_futures and **kwargs, no positional-or-keyword params; co_argcount counts only positional-or-keyword parameters, not *args). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "asyncio.Condition.__init__.__code__.co_name == '__init__'. Condition is a pure Python class in asyncio/locks.py; its __init__ code object's co_name is '__init__'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Condition.__init__.__code__.co_argcount == 2. Condition.__init__ signature is def __init__(self, lock=None): — 2 positional-or-keyword parameters (self + lock). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__init__.__code__.co_name == '__init__'. BoundedSemaphore is a pure Python class in asyncio/locks.py inheriting from Semaphore; its __init__ code object's co_name is '__init__'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__init__.__code__.co_argcount == 2. BoundedSemaphore.__init__ signature is def __init__(self, value=1): — 2 positional-or-keyword parameters (self + value). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.TaskGroup.__name__ == 'TaskGroup'. TaskGroup is a class defined in asyncio/taskgroups.py; its __name__ is 'TaskGroup'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.TaskGroup.__module__ == 'asyncio.taskgroups'. TaskGroup is defined in the asyncio.taskgroups submodule; its __module__ is 'asyncio.taskgroups'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.TaskGroup.__qualname__ == 'TaskGroup'. TaskGroup is a top-level class; its __qualname__ is 'TaskGroup'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.TaskGroup.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object'. TaskGroup inherits directly from object; __bases__[0].__name__ is 'object'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.TaskGroup.__mro__.__len__() == 2. TaskGroup's MRO is [TaskGroup, object] with length 2. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.gather.__code__.co_name == 'gather'. gather is a pure Python async function in asyncio/tasks.py; its code object's co_name is the function's simple name 'gather'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.gather.__code__.co_argcount == 0. gather signature uses *coros_or_futures and keyword-only return_exceptions; co_argcount counts only positional-or-keyword parameters, so it is 0. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

